1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:02,500
I heard you used to date

2
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:04,400
Kim Yeon Du.

3
00:00:05,700 --> 00:00:07,500
You

4
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:10,100
still like her, don't you?

5
00:00:11,900 --> 00:00:14,400
I like Do Ye Seok.

6
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:17,000
So do you want to

7
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,400
form an alliance with me?

8
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:26,800
No, I don't do such a thing.

9
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,600
We're in the same boat.

10
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,800
Do Ye Seok and I used to date,

11
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:41,300
just like you and her.

12
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:42,700
So what?

13
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,800
I'm still clinging to my ex,

14
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:48,040
just like you.

15
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:54,000
So I know exactly

16
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,400
how you feel right now.

17
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:01,200
You and Yeon Du don't even go to the same school.

18
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:04,400
You probably don't have a good reason to see her, as you're not together anymore.

19
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:07,500
You'll probably see her once a week, at the club at best.

20
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:09,500
Are you sure you're okay with that?

21
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:13,200
What are you trying to say?

22
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:15,200
Under this circumstance,

23
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:17,800
Do Ye Seok, who will see her at school, in the class, and at the club

24
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:20,700
dozens of times a day

25
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:23,600
has significant advantage.

26
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,960
I'll help you.

27
00:01:29,900 --> 00:01:33,000
So let's form an alliance.

28
00:01:41,848 --> 00:01:45,308
[Best Mistake 3]

29
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,700
Hello, Seol.

30
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:51,700
This is a picture of the sky I took today.

31
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:54,300
I wanted to give it to you.

32
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:57,800
I thought it could be useful for you to practice drawing.

33
00:01:57,800 --> 00:02:00,300
I thought it could be useful—

34
00:02:01,300 --> 00:02:04,300
I thought it could be useful for you—

35
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:07,700
Awkward.

36
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:09,500
So awkward.

37
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:10,895
Why can't you say it?

38
00:02:10,895 --> 00:02:13,700
Just be simple and charismatic.

39
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,500
I have a crush on you, Seol.

40
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:19,000
Seol.

41
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:22,300
Seol.

42
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,900
Seo Ju Ho?

43
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:34,000
Is there something going on between them?

44
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,700
Are they dating?

45
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:38,300
Did they use to date?

46
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:41,900
Or does he just have a crush on her like me?

47
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:46,400
Why does it matter? I hate all three scenarios.

48
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:51,800
Seol, I...

49
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,990
Seol...

50
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,500
Seol!

51
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:11,600
Oh?

52
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,000
This is...

53
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,300
a picture of the sky I took.

54
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:18,900
I thought you could use it for practicing drawing.

55
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:20,000
Oh, by the way,

56
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,300
what's wrong with your hand?

57
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:25,700
Oh, it's from the time when I was picking up the lipstick—

58
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:28,100
Oh, right, the lipstick!

59
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:34,400
What is this?

60
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,200
Why are you giving me this?

61
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:39,700
Thanks for saving me last time.

62
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:40,900
If it hadn't been for you,

63
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:43,600
I would've been hurt real bad.

64
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,600
Your lipstick got ruined

65
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:48,800
while you were trying to save me,

66
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:51,000
so I got a new one for you.

67
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:54,300
This many, though?

68
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:57,000
I didn't know what color the lipstick was.

69
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,200
But, I mean,

70
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:01,200
there is no such a thing as the same color in the universe.

71
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:07,400
Don't you have the same color?

72
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,300
No,

73
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:11,300
there is no such a thing as the same color in the universe.

74
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,300
I should get going.

75
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:35,700
Yeah.

76
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:37,700
I just got here.

77
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:40,600
The second cabinet, right?

78
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,800
I'll leave it here, then.

79
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:49,000
Okay.

80
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,900
Yeah.

81
00:05:58,001 --> 00:06:00,609
She must've been tired.

82
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:19,400
I dozed off.

83
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,200
Did someone drop by?

84
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:37,100
Good job. Your pictures are nice.

85
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:40,190
Senior Ye Seok must've dropped by.

86
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:04,900
Oh my! I'm late!

87
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:08,000
They said they would cancel the lesson if I were late.

88
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,100
Guys!

89
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:24,900
It looks like you'd shoot laser beams from your eyes.

90
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:26,200
5.

91
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,300
4.

92
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,400
3.

93
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:29,500
2.

94
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:31,000
1.

95
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:35,800
I'm on time, right?

96
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,700
Ta-da!

97
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:00,400
Have it while studying.

98
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,541
I picked it up myself

99
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,600
as delivery was backed up.

100
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:06,400
You guys' favorite fried chicken.

101
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:13,400
You mean Ji Seong's favorite?

102
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:17,400
People would think you're his mom or something.

103
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,400
Teacher,

104
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:21,370
Please take care of my Ji Seong.

105
00:09:26,338 --> 00:09:28,200
It's okay to eat,

106
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:31,200
but make sure to study.

107
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,300
Squirtle.

108
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:34,300
How can you possibly talk about studying

109
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:36,500
when there is holy fried chicken in front of you?

110
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,600
I'm your teacher. Don't call me Squirtle!

111
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,400
Right, Noona—

112
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,000
I mean, Teacher.

113
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,400
I can't really focus, anyway.

114
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,900
Shall we just play games while eating chicken, instead?

115
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:46,900
Yes, yes, yes!

116
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:48,400
Playing games is the best way

117
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:50,100
to work on lacked concentration.

118
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:51,400
How about Mafia?

119
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:53,800
Nah, you can't play that with just three people!

120
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,200
Instead of that,

121
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:57,200
how about charades?

122
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,900
Ah Hun's very good at it.

123
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,000
Hey, guys.

124
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,000
- About games—
- Hey!

125
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,900
Ji Seong's an expert.

126
00:10:03,900 --> 00:10:06,600
How many do you usually get in a minute?

127
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,964
That's not important right—

128
00:10:07,964 --> 00:10:09,500
Ji Seong gets everything right.

129
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:10,400
How about you?

130
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:12,200
How many do you usually get in a minute?

131
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:15,400
Ah Hun has never counted them before so she doesn't know,

132
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:19,310
because Ah Hun always gets all of them right.

133
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:27,500
Are you up for a challenge to see who wins?

134
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:29,700
Did you just challenge Ji Seong?

135
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:30,700
Guys.

136
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:33,000
Now is not the time to—

137
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,500
Wait a second.

138
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,800
A challenge?

139
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,300
Game challenge?

140
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:42,200
Yes, let's do it.

141
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,500
Okay, let's do it.

142
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:44,400
Cool!

143
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:45,500
Sorry?

144
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:47,500
Game challenge.

145
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:53,500
[Good Job Compliment Grapes]

146
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:55,000
What is this?

147
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,500
Grapes?

148
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,200
These are not just grapes.

149
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,100
Grapes of victory.

150
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:02,800
Grapes of victory?

151
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,900
You two are going to challenge each other.

152
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:06,900
Whoever wins,

153
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:08,600
gets this sticker each time,

154
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,744
and whoever completes

155
00:11:09,744 --> 00:11:12,300
the bunch of grapes first—

156
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,400
And then?

157
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:16,400
And then?

158
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:27,100
That person

159
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:30,000
becomes the true winner.

160
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,200
Meh, still.

161
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:44,200
Shouldn't you give them prizes at least?

162
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,600
Who would do it just for that?

163
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,800
Okay.

164
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:49,900
The true winner.

165
00:11:49,900 --> 00:11:51,300
That's for Ji Seong!

166
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:52,500
What are you talking about?

167
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,399
That's for Ah Hun!

168
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:58,900
They're going to do it.

169
00:11:58,900 --> 00:11:59,800
Alright.

170
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,500
Let's start with an English vocabulary test—

171
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:04,500
No, I meant an English vocabulary game.

172
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,300
Ji Seong's ready. Let's start.

173
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,200
Ah Hun's ready, too.

174
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:12,000
I'm going to win.

175
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,400
You're here.

176
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:27,000
What's the thing you said you had to tell me about Kim Yeon Du?

177
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,900
Having an alliance is nice.

178
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:32,000
Look at you coming here after just one call.

179
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,000
Don't tell me...

180
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,800
Do you want a drink?

181
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:39,000
Enjoy it yourself.

182
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,400
Stay here for a bit.

183
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:47,600
What are you trying to pull?

184
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,800
Nothing.

185
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:52,400
Please, just drink with me.

186
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:54,400
Just for today.

187
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:58,700
I've broken up with my ex, who was my only friend.

188
00:12:58,700 --> 00:12:59,958
Classmates

189
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:03,500
say I'm the bitch who dumped her ex.

190
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:06,900
So I've got no one to drink with.

191
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:09,200
It's so lame, isn't it?

192
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:13,000
It doesn't have anything to do with me.

193
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,700
Alright.

194
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:18,400
Should we start talking about Kim Yeon Du then?

195
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:20,200
Kim Yeon Du and Do Ye Soek...

196
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,600
Did you know they've been meeting up alone,

197
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:23,722
once or twice a week?

198
00:13:23,722 --> 00:13:25,200
Why is she meeting that bastard?

199
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,000
For a group assignment.

200
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,700
It looks like they're in the same group.

201
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:30,800
Dammit.

202
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:33,300
Why that bastard of all people?

203
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,200
Anyway,

204
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:44,200
it looks like they see each other often lately.

205
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:48,100
It seems like she can't take a hint.

206
00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:49,600
Sorry?

207
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:51,400
They study the same major, take the same class,

208
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,300
and do group meetings alone.

209
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:54,222
It looked like

210
00:13:54,222 --> 00:13:56,800
they were going to the school cafeteria together as well.

211
00:13:56,800 --> 00:14:00,600
It's only a matter of time before people start gossiping about them.

212
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:02,200
But she always says yes.

213
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,330
When he asks her to meet up,

214
00:14:03,330 --> 00:14:05,400
she shows up, smiling.

215
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:06,900
She doesn't know how to say no,

216
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:08,400
frustratingly.

217
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:11,200
That's how she is.

218
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:14,000
She can't take a hint,

219
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,300
which makes you frustrated sometimes.

220
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:17,000
Right.

221
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,800
- She is like that.
- But because of that,

222
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:23,400
she's not calculating by nature.

223
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:24,738
She doesn't take care of herself,

224
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:28,100
but she always puts others first.

225
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,500
That's how she is.

226
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:32,000
She is too kind like that.

227
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:38,700
She never gets swayed, though.

228
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:40,900
You might think she would be swayed easily because she is kind.

229
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:42,690
But she is not.

230
00:14:42,690 --> 00:14:45,400
If anyone were swayed, it would be me.

231
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:49,000
Right.

232
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:53,000
I told her that I wanted to break up first.

233
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,700
You...

234
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:58,000
don't hate her?

235
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:01,600
She dumped you anyway.

236
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:03,700
You don't hate her even after that?

237
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:10,700
She must've had a good reason.

238
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:23,600
There must be a good enough reason

239
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:26,800
if Yeon Du got swayed.

240
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:29,650
And I want to know what that reason was.

241
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:44,600
Why are you staring at me?

242
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,300
Nothing.

243
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:49,080
Thanks for being my drinking buddy tonight.

244
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:08,500
Hyung!

245
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:10,500
Do you still have a lot left?

246
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,500
I'm done!

247
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:15,600
Let me see.

248
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,000
Wow!

249
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:24,200
Your answers are exactly the same as mine.

250
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:26,300
- Really?
- Yes!

251
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:28,300
We must've got everything right.

252
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:30,900
Are we getting full marks today?

253
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,200
If we get full marks,

254
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:34,800
we won't have to go over the wrong answers today.

255
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,400
Question number one, two.

256
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,500
Question number two, three.

257
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:48,100
Question number three, four.

258
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:50,700
Question number four, four.

259
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:57,000
Question number five, three.

260
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,500
Question number six, one.

261
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:02,500
Question number seven, two.

262
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:05,400
Question number eight, one.

263
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:11,600
It wasn't that we both got them right,

264
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:14,400
but we both got them wrong.

265
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:27,700
What are you doing?

266
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:34,900
Teacher!

267
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,500
It's time to start.

268
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:39,400
Wait, is that Squirtle?

269
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:40,677
This is about

270
00:17:40,677 --> 00:17:43,000
a logarithmic function.

271
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,349
First of all, this log function,

272
00:17:44,349 --> 00:17:46,800
passes 0 comma 1,

273
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,300
so what is the value of X1?

274
00:17:51,503 --> 00:17:52,569
Wow,

275
00:17:52,569 --> 00:17:54,100
this is so cool.

276
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:56,300
It looks like it will help you focus, too.

277
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:58,700
Ji Seong wants to get tutoring on an iPad,

278
00:17:58,700 --> 00:18:00,600
instead of going to an academy.

279
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,600
So the answer will be...

280
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,300
Number one!

281
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:07,000
You've got it.

282
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,100
Let's do it together, Hyung.

283
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:13,200
Ah Hun's going to study hard

284
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:16,474
till the SATs, using this.

285
00:18:16,474 --> 00:18:18,400
We got this!

286
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:20,300
We got this!

287
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:28,400
Here it is.

288
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:34,600
Thanks for the coffee and organizing the pictures.

289
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:36,200
No worries.

290
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:38,200
It's nothing.

291
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:40,900
Then,

292
00:18:40,900 --> 00:18:43,400
shall we start with the second assignment?

293
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,500
Yeah,

294
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:46,000
let's do.

295
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,800
Excuse me, Senior.

296
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,400
Yeah?

297
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,900
Shall we

298
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:29,300
go to the library?

299
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:31,800
Or a study café?

300
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:37,300
Do you feel uncomfortable

301
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:39,400
being alone with me?

302
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:40,600
Sorry?

303
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:41,800
No.

304
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:44,300
That's not what I meant.

305
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,500
It's just

306
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:48,800
that it feels a bit awkward

307
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:50,900
to be alone with you

308
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:54,100
in an empty classroom.

309
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:57,000
On top of that, people might get the wrong idea.

310
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,700
We're just

311
00:19:58,700 --> 00:20:01,300
doing the assignment here

312
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:02,800
because it happens to be empty.

313
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,700
It didn't just happen to be empty.

314
00:20:04,700 --> 00:20:06,300
Sorry?

315
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,800
I made them leave

316
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:13,000
because I wanted to be alone with you.

317
00:20:28,045 --> 00:20:31,409
[Best Mistake 3]

318
00:20:31,409 --> 00:20:34,551
[Bonus clip]

319
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:43,600
Teacher!

320
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:44,800
It's time to start the class.

321
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:45,800
What's this?

322
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:47,200
Ji Seong wants to get tutoring on an iPad,

323
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:49,550
instead of going to an academy.

324
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:57,460
♫ Even if it hurts, we still cross the lines ♫

325
00:20:57,460 --> 00:20:59,860
♫ It's getting perfect again ♫

326
00:20:59,860 --> 00:21:02,700
♫ Even though it gets pretty comfortable ♫

327
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:04,300
[Next episode]
Chew thoroughly and eat slowly.

328
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:05,255
I'll make you some more if you want.

329
00:21:05,255 --> 00:21:06,817
I like Seol but she doesn't like me back?

330
00:21:06,817 --> 00:21:07,600
That's good.

331
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:08,826
It's all because of you.

332
00:21:08,826 --> 00:21:09,868
Stop talking back to me.

333
00:21:09,868 --> 00:21:11,094
Ju Ho has a crush on you, Seol?

334
00:21:11,094 --> 00:21:12,500
It would be nice if you gave me a chance.

335
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,524
But looking back,

336
00:21:14,524 --> 00:21:17,000
that was a good memory, wasn't it?

337
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,600
She totally used poor Ye Seok.

338
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:20,600
What's going on?

339
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:23,000
Annoying.

340
00:21:25,168 --> 00:21:30,768
♫ Want to know what happens next? Play Best Mistake! ♫

341
